text: South Moluccas, also called South Maluku, is an unrecognised nation in the islands of Indonesia. The current population sits at around 1,881,727 people. There is no observed capital but the largest city is Ambon. There are 150 islands but the main ones are Ceram, Ambon and Buru. They are currently not a country though it is being disputed. Not much is known about the place. Category:Indonesia
title: Republic of South Maluku
